&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We Are &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Verve has created a more efficient and privacy-focused way to buy and monetize advertising. Verve is an ecosystem of demand and supply technologies fusing data, media, and technology together to deliver results and growth to both advertisers and publishers–no matter the screen or location, no matter who, what, or where a customer is. With 30 offices across the globe and with an eye on servicing forward-thinking advertising customers, Verve’s solutions are trusted by more than 90 of the United States’ top 100 advertisers, 4,000 publishers globally, and the world’s top demand-side platforms. Learn more at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://verve.com/&quot;&gt;verve.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll work within the core team to implement, optimize, and scale Verve&#39;s &lt;strong&gt;Android HyBid SDK ecosystem&lt;/strong&gt;, turning architectural initiatives into reliable, production-ready modules running across millions of end-user devices. This is library and SDK work, with all the memory, threading, and performance constraints that come with running inside external host applications, so understanding the difference between SDK development and standard app development matters here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring across &lt;strong&gt;two levels on the same team&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Level II (Engineer II):&lt;/strong&gt; you take well-defined specifications and turn them into high-quality, predictable implementations, collaborating closely with the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Level III (Senior):&lt;/strong&gt; you provide technical leadership, architectural vision, and end-to-end ownership of the SDK, working with a high degree of autonomy and mentoring others along the way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SDK Core Development &amp;amp; Architecture: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop, refine, and optimize critical submodules of the Android HyBid SDK, and at the senior level, architect and lead its evolution, focusing on safe multi-threaded execution, low memory footprints, binary-size budgets, backward compatibility, and crash-free integration into diverse host applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Collaboration: &lt;/strong&gt;Partner with product managers and business stakeholders to estimate feature effort, refine technical requirements, and prioritize delivery, from sprint-level scope to strategic SDK roadmaps driven by technical feasibility and business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Platform Parity: &lt;/strong&gt;Work alongside the iOS team, reading and navigating the Swift/Objective-C codebase to cross-reference logic, guarantee behavioral consistency, and keep release scopes synchronized across platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Collaboration, Quality &amp;amp; Leadership: &lt;/strong&gt;Contribute to technical refinement sessions, code reviews, documentation, and bug-resolution cycles, and as you grow, set core standards (binary-size budgets, backward-compatibility validation) and mentor mid-level engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architecture &amp;amp; Privacy:&lt;/strong&gt; Implement, update, and test the integration layers supporting Google&#39;s Android Privacy Sandbox (Topics API, SDK Runtime modules) and user-consent data pipelines (GDPR/TCF 2.x). At the senior level, lead their structural design, translating strict privacy regulations into high-performance SDK code.&lt;/li&gt;
